# Doc locale parity (en / fa / zh)

Whenever you change a **hand-written** documentation page, the same path under all three locale trees must exist and stay **content-equivalent**.

| Locale | Path |
|--------|------|
| English | `docs/en/{section}/…/page.md` |
| Persian (RTL) | `docs/fa/{section}/…/page.md` |
| Chinese | `docs/zh/{section}/…/page.md` |

Root README uses `.cursor/rules/readme-i18n.mdc` instead.

## Resolve the page trio

From any edited file, derive the logical key (relative to `docs/en/`, no `.md`):

- `docs/fa/cheatsheet/cli/rgw.md` → `cheatsheet/cli/rgw`
- `docs/en/arch/index.md` → `arch/index`

Required siblings: `docs/en/{key}.md`, `docs/fa/{key}.md`, `docs/zh/{key}.md`.

## When you edit **any one** of the three

1. Apply the **same structural change** to the other two (headings, lists, tables, bash blocks, internal links).
2. Translate new/changed **prose** into fa and zh.
3. Keep CLI flags, option names, and `<placeholders>` untranslated.
4. Run the matching sync (see below) before finishing.
5. Run `python3 scripts/generate-content-inventory.py`.

## Where to put translations

| Page kind | Update fa/zh in |
|-----------|-----------------|
| `HAND_PAGES` | `scripts/locales/pages/*.yaml` **or** `docs/fa/…` / `docs/zh/…` directly |
| Section hubs | All three locale files directly (identical HTML structure) |
| Root README | `scripts/locales/pages/readme.yaml` → `make readme` |
| Generated guides / config | Re-run the generator — do not hand-edit one locale alone |
| `arch/rgw/` | `sync-rgw-from-docs-extended.py` + locale YAML |

## Sync commands

```bash
python3 scripts/sync-i18n-pages.py
python3 scripts/sync-i18n-config.py
make readme
python3 scripts/regenerate-docs.py
python3 scripts/validate-docs-paths.py
```

## Exceptions (English-only)

- `docs/en/cheatsheet/config/<subsystem>/*.md` option tables (generated)
- `reports/` — generated inventory
- Files from `generate-config.py`, `generate-*-guide.py`, `sync-rgw-from-docs-extended.py`

## Do not

- Ship a nav page with only `docs/en/…` and no fa/zh siblings
- Edit `docs/fa/…` without updating `docs/en/…` when structure changed
- Reintroduce `.fa.md` / `.zh.md` suffix files
